                     <interp inst="t18320105-54-person623" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am pot-boy to Mr. Goseley, who <rs id="t18320105-54-viclabel301" type="occupation">keeps the Swan public-house, in Foley-place</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-54-victim620 t18320105-54-viclabel301"></join> - the prisoner was given to me by Phillips, at the corner of Norton-street, with these two pint pots, one of which, is my master's; the prisoner said, "I hope this young man will be as merciful as he can, it is the first I ever took belonging to you."</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Had you made him any promise? A. No; he went very quietly.</p>
